Bank Financial Project for stock prices Data Analysis and Vizualization¶

1. In this Project we mainly focus on exploratory data analysis of stock prices.¶

2. This project is basically made for to use of the libraries like Numpy, Pandas, matplotlib, seaborn,plotly and cufflinks.¶

3. The data is based on Bank Stocks and see it progressed throughout the financial crisis all the way early to 2016.¶

In [ ]:
# import the needed Libraries
In [1]:
from pandas_datareader import data, wb
import numpy as np 
import pandas as pd 
import datetime 
import seaborn as sns 
%matplotlib inline

Dataset¶

We need to get data using datareader. we will get the stock information for the following banks:¶

Bank of America¶

City Group¶

Goldman Sachs¶

JPMorgan Chase¶

Morgan Stanley¶

Wells Fargo¶

We need to figure out how to get the stock data from Jan 1st 2006 to Jan 1st 2016 for each of this banks.¶

So, First we need to set each bank to the seprate dataframe, with the variable name for that bank being its ticker symbol. This will involve a few steps:¶

1. Use datetime to start and end datetime objects.¶

2. Figure out the ticker symbol for each bank.¶

3. Figure out how to use datareader to grab info on the stock.¶
